This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on learning sense embeddings for words. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes an unsupervised model that uses a modified Gumbel softmax function, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and falls under the category of probabilistic modeling and inference, which is covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks to learn sense embeddings, which is a common technique in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions downstream evaluations, which could involve tasks such as classification or prediction, which are common in the field of neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing, which is often associated with computer vision and image processing (cs.CV) due to the use of convolutional neural networks for text classification and other tasks.
